1
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:21,521
H-Hello! I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!

2
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:31,406
A love at first sight… kind of thing.

3
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:33,283
Oh…

4
00:00:34,784 --> 00:00:35,952
Um…

5
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:42,625
Let's start off as friends… kind of thing.

6
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,064
Seiichi?

7
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:13,448
-This is the best way to carry it.
-No way.

8
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:16,076
You look like a beetle from this angle.

9
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,329
-Seiichi. Hurry up.
-Okay.

10
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:20,371
-Go!
-All right!

11
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,499
Go, Seiichi! You can do it!

12
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:24,000
-Super scrappy!
-Huh?

13
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:26,086
-Super scrappy!
-What?

14
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,754
Super scrappy!

15
00:01:27,837 --> 00:01:28,671
Yay!

16
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:35,303
I'll take your marriage registration form.

17
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:36,721
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

18
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,389
Congratulations.

19
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,767
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

20
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:42,602
-Yes!
-Yeah.

21
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:46,606
I'm looking forward to our life together.

22
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,192
Yeah.

23
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:51,653
Ready?

24
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,656
Say cheese.

25
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:04,249
<i>Oh, man! I just thought of something!</i>

26
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:06,584
<i>Wouldn't "Kanau" be a great name?</i>

27
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:21,432
I'm home.

28
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:33,486
JULY 4TH, 2018

29
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,488
Please come closer.

30
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:52,881
We will now close the door.

31
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:56,092
Please say your final farewells.

32
00:02:58,469 --> 00:02:59,888
Seiichi.

33
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:03,433
Seiichi.

34
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:31,252
He was such a kind boy.

35
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:39,677
Why did this have to happen?

36
00:03:44,515 --> 00:03:46,768
We all got to see him off, didn't we?

37
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,898
It wasn't all of us.

38
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:58,988
I'm sorry

39
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:03,534
that my relatives were unable to attend.

40
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,165
What could you do?

41
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:14,462
They must have better things to do.

42
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:15,880
Hush.

43
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:26,432
What will you do about the baby?

44
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:32,855
I will raise the baby with care.

45
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:37,819
But wouldn't it be hard on your own?

46
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:44,617
You probably don't have many people
in Tokyo who can help you.

47
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:46,953
How about this?

48
00:04:47,036 --> 00:04:52,625
You can quit your job
and raise the baby with us in Fukuoka.

49
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:00,550
Thank you, but…

50
00:05:01,843 --> 00:05:05,096
I'm not quitting my job.

51
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:09,100
I'll figure things out on my own…

52
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:16,524
Raising a child is no easy task.

53
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:23,614
Your mother was too busy
to attend her son-in-law's funeral.

54
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:29,829
She won't offer you any help, will she?

55
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:30,830
Don't say that.

56
00:05:30,913 --> 00:05:32,248
What?

57
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:44,635
I'll be fine.

58
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:50,224
"Fine"?

59
00:05:53,936 --> 00:05:58,399
The child of our dearest son

60
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:02,278
is a precious grandchild to us.

61
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:05,531
Sumiko.

62
00:06:06,115 --> 00:06:09,786
What I'm saying is,
your child isn't just yours alone.

63
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:15,833
You need to give that a lot of thought.

64
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:17,543
Otherwise…

65
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:23,216
it's your child who will end up
going through hardship.

66
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:40,400
Funerals in Japan are quiet.

67
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:42,985
Yeah.

68
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:47,698
In Korea, it's a lot noisier.

69
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:55,581
We cry out loud more, drink alcohol,

70
00:06:57,291 --> 00:07:01,629
share memories, and get drunk.

71
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,009
I see.

72
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:15,518
I'm sure Seiichi would want…

73
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:22,233
everyone to live happily.

74
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,320
You're right.

75
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:34,996
The ones left behind have to go on…

76
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:40,209
living happy, fulfilling lives.

77
00:07:44,213 --> 00:07:45,339
Right?

78
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,102
Let’s go home and share a few drinks.

79
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:11,324
Let's drink.

80
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:20,917
Ms. Sasaki, would you like some potatoes?

81
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,960
All right. Here.

82
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:25,379
It's okay. Here, let's eat.

83
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,634
Ms. Sasaki.

84
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:33,054
They're warm and tasty, you know.

85
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:35,765
Here.

86
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:40,228
Don't take too long, okay?

87
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:43,147
We have many other residents
who need help too.

88
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,357
Yes, sir.

89
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:47,151
Yes, sir.

90
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:52,615
Here. Try the fish.

91
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:02,124
Are you okay?

92
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,545
You have time to worry about others, huh?

93
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:08,464
I'm sorry.

94
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,135
I'm fine.

95
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:23,271
Caregiving is a good job, don't you think?

96
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:25,523
Huh?

97
00:09:26,774 --> 00:09:27,817
Never mind.

98
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:29,151
Bye.

99
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,536
Good work today.

100
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,465
I'm home.

101
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:53,259
Welcome home.

102
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:59,473
Whoa. Thanks.

103
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:00,558
Yeah.

104
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:22,246
What? Aren't you gonna eat?

105
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:24,707
Yeah, I will.

106
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,793
Thanks for the meal.

107
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,421
Eat it with the bread.

108
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:31,839
-This?
-Yeah.

109
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:40,514
Mm, this is good.

110
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:54,445
Are you in touch with Sumiko?

111
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:57,323
Kind of.

112
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,660
How has she been lately?

113
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:06,957
Her company allows her
to take maternity and childcare leave.

114
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:11,962
She can take time off,
so she said she'd be okay.

115
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:16,425
But that can't be true, huh?

116
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,892
How about we go visit soon?

117
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:30,314
Let's go see Sumiko.

118
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,820
We're coming in.

119
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,129
Sumiko.

120
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:38,466
Ryu?

121
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,219
And Johan too?

122
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:46,182
Wait. Was the door unlocked?

123
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,266
Yeah.

124
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,228
Sorry about the mess.

125
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:54,148
I'll clean up, so just give me a second.

126
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:09,413
It's fine. Don't mind us.

127
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:15,503
What do you mean?

128
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:19,006
Huh?

129
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:21,550
What do you mean, "it's fine"?

130
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,594
Uh…

131
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:26,639
-I mean--
-It must be nice having Johan with you.

132
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:28,390
Huh?

133
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:30,184
You're not alone.

134
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:33,187
You're not lonely.

135
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:34,980
Huh?

136
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:37,149
It's not fair.

137
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:39,860
Isn't this messed up?

138
00:13:41,862 --> 00:13:42,947
Why?

139
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:58,796
Why did Seiichi have to die?

140
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:04,510
I don't get it.

141
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:08,597
I just don't get it at all.

142
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,353
Sumiko.

143
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:20,401
You could ask your family for help.

144
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,820
I don't have any family.

145
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,574
I mean,

146
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:31,954
if he was gonna leave me by myself,
he shouldn't have married me.

147
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:36,458
And a baby, on top of that?

148
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:39,545
A b-baby…

149
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,547
Why?

150
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:48,053
If he was gonna leave
the two of us behind…

151
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:52,182
then…

152
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,444
Calm down.

153
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:08,824
I can't become a mother.

154
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,913
Someone like me,
raised by a mother like that,

155
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:17,583
could never become a parent.

156
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,503
Sumiko.

157
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:27,343
You're not alone.

158
00:15:29,553 --> 00:15:32,473
My mom and dad

159
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,893
care about you too.

160
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:49,907
How about we make a trip to Nasu together?

161
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:24,441
All right, we're here.

162
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:29,113
Wow, it's been a while.

163
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:34,827
Okay.

164
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:37,538
-All right.
-Leave the bags to me.

165
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,790
-What? Can you handle them?
-Yeah.

166
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,835
-There.
-You're so strong.

167
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:46,630
Welcome home.

168
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:48,007
I'm home.

169
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,759
Tadashi is still at work.

170
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,928
I'm sure he'll be back soon.

171
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:55,055
-It's been a while, huh?
-Yeah.

172
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:56,765
Hey, wait. The key.

173
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:57,850
Oh, right.

174
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,351
-Here.
-Thanks.

175
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:21,749
There.

176
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:26,754
That house with the red roof
is where my family lives.

177
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:31,717
We're family after all.

178
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:34,887
And sometimes,

179
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:38,932
being family makes it harder
to rely on them.

180
00:17:57,701 --> 00:17:59,119
You sure eat a lot.

181
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:01,497
-Johan, do you want more <i>somen</i>?
-Yes, please.

182
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,873
Coming right up.

183
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,834
-He can really eat.
-Yeah.

184
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:08,378
Do you have <i>somen </i>like this in Korea too?

185
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:10,756
-Yeah, we have the noodles.
-Yeah?

186
00:18:10,839 --> 00:18:13,967
But we don't dip them in <i>tsuyu </i>like this.

187
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,177
-One serving each?
-Yeah.

188
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,221
-Oh, I see.
-We each get our own bowl.

189
00:18:17,304 --> 00:18:19,765
-Sumiko, are you able to eat?
-Yeah.

190
00:18:19,848 --> 00:18:21,183
-I'm eating.
-Eat a lot, okay?

191
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:22,601
Thank you.

192
00:18:22,684 --> 00:18:24,561
Your <i>nasu </i>is the best, Auntie.

193
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:25,938
-Really?
-Yeah.

194
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:28,816
-Yeah, it's good.
-No place like Nasu for <i>nasu</i>.

195
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:31,151
Whoa, you learned stuff like that too?

196
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:32,236
Yeah.

197
00:19:42,055 --> 00:19:43,056
Hey.

198
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,851
What? Hurry up and get changed.

199
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:47,686
But it's still four o'clock.

200
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:50,105
That's when the fish are biting.

201
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,399
You wanna catch <i>euneo</i>, Johan?

202
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:53,859
Right? Let's go fishing!

203
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:56,570
Hey, come on. Get ready.

204
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:58,947
-Come on. Let's go fishing!
-Okay, okay.

205
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:01,617
-Let's go.
-It's so early.

206
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,410
We're gonna catch <i>euneo</i>!

207
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:20,552
They're not biting, huh?

208
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:25,182
The fish won't be caught that easily.

209
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:27,267
Okay.

210
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:46,328
Thank you.

211
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,997
Huh? For what?

212
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:54,503
Back when I quit ice hockey,

213
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:56,713
thank you for not saying anything.

214
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:01,385
What's this, all of a sudden?

215
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:11,603
Oh!

216
00:21:11,687 --> 00:21:13,313
I got a bite!

217
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:16,275
-Where?
-Don't panic.

218
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:20,028
Reel it in slowly. Good.

219
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:21,947
-Whoa!
-Keep going. Just like that.

220
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:23,949
It's here! Can I pull it in now?

221
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:27,452
-All right.
-There. It's in!

222
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,162
Look at that!

223
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:31,707
Johan!

224
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:33,208
Yeah!

225
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:36,503
-Look!
-Whoa!

226
00:21:36,586 --> 00:21:38,672
-Sweetfish.
-Wow.

227
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:41,591
<i>-Euneo</i>?
-Yeah, <i>euneo</i>. This is amazing.

228
00:21:43,218 --> 00:21:44,261
-Whoa.
-Whoa.

229
00:21:44,344 --> 00:21:46,138
-It was a bit weak.
-Impressive.

230
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:47,222
Whoa.

231
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:49,224
-Just a bit more.
-Too weak.

232
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:51,143
Go!

233
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,811
-Wow!
-Wow!

234
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:55,939
-How's that?
-Amazing! It skipped a lot.

235
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:57,941
-All right.
-Wow, the Narutaki family.

236
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,574
-Whoa, that was amazing.
-Wow.

237
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:06,700
Nice one.

238
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:40,776
Did you sleep well?

239
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,320
-Yeah.
-Good.

240
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:46,573
-That's…
-Mm-hmm.

241
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:49,368
Brings back memories.

242
00:22:52,245 --> 00:22:56,083
You were cute since you were little.

243
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:03,840
My mother didn't care about me at all,

244
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:08,512
so maybe that's why I got to go
to so many places with you guys instead.

245
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:13,809
Sumiko.

246
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:23,902
Would you like to
have your child here with us?

247
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:29,616
What?

248
00:23:29,699 --> 00:23:34,871
Things like blood relations are a curse.

249
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:38,250
Being family doesn't mean
you understand each other.

250
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:42,212
That's just wishful thinking.

251
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:46,466
I…

252
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:50,220
I was like that

253
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:53,014
with my parents too.

254
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:59,604
You and your mother

255
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:02,774
are nothing alike.

256
00:24:06,319 --> 00:24:08,572
You don't need to worry about a thing.

257
00:24:09,614 --> 00:24:10,615
Okay?

258
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:18,290
You're always welcome in our home.

259
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:23,295
We may not be blood-related…

260
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:28,467
but you'll always have a home with us.

261
00:24:33,096 --> 00:24:34,097
Right?

262
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:36,308
Oh!

263
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,227
Yes, okay.

264
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:41,521
It's your home.

265
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:45,317
Yeah.

266
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:54,034
I…

267
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,329
I've been given so much

268
00:24:58,830 --> 00:25:01,416
by so many people.

269
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:10,675
This guy too.

270
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,386
He's given me a lot.

271
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:40,622
Sumiko.

272
00:25:44,334 --> 00:25:45,752
Why don't you…

273
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:50,090
come live with us?

274
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:53,885
What?

275
00:26:04,312 --> 00:26:05,814
That's what I want too.

276
00:26:27,627 --> 00:26:29,504
The baby's name.

277
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:33,717
It's Kanau.

278
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:39,431
Kanau?

279
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:49,107
It's written with characters that mean
"dreams come true" and "universe."

280
00:26:50,609 --> 00:26:51,818
Kanau.

281
00:26:56,615 --> 00:26:59,826
Super Scrappy Seiichi came up with it.

282
00:27:37,447 --> 00:27:38,948
All right.

283
00:28:37,924 --> 00:28:39,551
The baby was delivered safely.

284
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:42,595
Please wait while we complete
some procedures.

285
00:28:45,056 --> 00:28:48,143
The mother is recovering well too.

286
00:28:49,644 --> 00:28:51,730
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

287
00:28:59,612 --> 00:29:01,698
Man, the baby is here.

288
00:29:01,781 --> 00:29:03,366
It's here, huh?

289
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:05,618
What a relief.

290
00:29:05,702 --> 00:29:08,913
Oh, man. Kanau.

291
00:29:10,248 --> 00:29:11,666
Wow.

292
00:29:26,097 --> 00:29:28,016
-Kanau.
-Kanau.

293
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:29,434
Kanau.

294
00:29:29,934 --> 00:29:30,769
Wow.

295
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:31,895
So small.

296
00:29:31,978 --> 00:29:34,689
So wrinkly. Cute.

297
00:29:35,356 --> 00:29:37,358
-Kanau.
-Oh, she smiled!

298
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:39,235
-Kanau!
-You smiled!

299
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:41,070
Over here. Peekaboo!

300
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:43,865
-Here! She's looking this way!
-She looked this way.

301
00:29:43,948 --> 00:29:44,866
-Kanau!
-Kanau!

302
00:29:44,949 --> 00:29:46,159
-Is she looking?
-Yeah.

303
00:29:46,242 --> 00:29:47,327
-Is she?
-She is.

304
00:29:47,410 --> 00:29:49,662
-Kanau!
-You're incredible!

305
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:50,705
-Hello.
<i>-</i>So cute.

306
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:52,791
-Do you see us, Kanau?
-She smiled.

307
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:58,713
-Ryu is setting up the crib for us.
-There we go.

308
00:29:58,797 --> 00:30:00,799
Isn't that great, Kanau?

309
00:30:00,882 --> 00:30:02,634
-Kanau!
-Kanau, look over here.

310
00:30:02,717 --> 00:30:03,718
Over here.

311
00:30:06,721 --> 00:30:08,848
Johan got you a toy.

312
00:30:08,932 --> 00:30:09,808
Argh!

313
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:11,851
-Huh? Ryu, are you okay?
-Keep it down!

314
00:30:11,935 --> 00:30:13,144
Help me out.

315
00:30:13,228 --> 00:30:15,647
-You gotta stick this in. This one.
-Okay.

316
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:17,816
-Down there.
-Okay.

317
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:20,819
-Ready?
-Okay.

318
00:30:23,696 --> 00:30:26,282
Huh?

319
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:28,701
Yes, we did it!

320
00:30:29,744 --> 00:30:36,292
<i>The stars shining above us</i>
<i>have created countless stories.</i>

321
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:42,215
<i>One of them is loved all across Japan.</i>

322
00:30:42,298 --> 00:30:44,467
<i>Night on the Galactic Railroad.</i>

323
00:30:44,551 --> 00:30:45,510
Kanau.

324
00:30:45,593 --> 00:30:47,011
<i>"Campanella."</i>

325
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:50,723
<i>"It's just the two of us alone again."</i>

326
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:54,060
<i>"Let's go on together, as far as we can."</i>

327
00:30:54,727 --> 00:30:56,688
<i>"I'm no longer afraid."</i>

328
00:30:57,981 --> 00:31:03,403
<i>"Just like that scorpion,</i>
<i>if it's truly for everyone's happiness,</i>

329
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:08,658
<i>I don't care what happens to my body."</i>

330
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:11,035
<i>"Yes."</i>

331
00:31:12,078 --> 00:31:13,788
<i>"I feel the same way."</i>

332
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:16,040
<i>"But I wonder…"</i>

333
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:20,879
<i>"What is true happiness?"</i>

334
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:26,009
<i>"I still don't know."</i>

335
00:31:27,677 --> 00:31:29,012
I know what it is.

336
00:31:29,971 --> 00:31:30,805
Hmm?

337
00:31:36,686 --> 00:31:37,687
Right?

338
00:33:56,367 --> 00:33:59,287
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
